[38;5;129mтФВ[0m thoughts:                                                                                                                                                                            [38;5;129mтФВ[0m
[38;5;129mтФВ[0m The IDOR vulnerability testing has confirmed that this application has proper session-based access control. The Flask session cookies are cryptographically signed, preventing the   [38;5;129mтФВ[0m
[38;5;129mтФВ[0m IDOR vector through cookie tampering. The user_id form parameter appears to be properly validated against the session-stored user_id rather than blindly trusting client input.      [38;5;129mтФВ[0m
[38;5;129mтФВ[0m                                                                                                                                                                                      [38;5;129mтФВ[0m
[38;5;129mтФВ[0m However, there is one interesting finding: the `/password/<username>` endpoint appears to be username-aware, only returning the password form for the authenticated user ("test").   [38;5;129mтФВ[0m
[38;5;129mтФВ[0m All other usernames return 302 redirects. This could indicate that:                                                                                                                  [38;5;129mтФВ[0m
[38;5;129mтФВ[0m 1. The authentication flow is two-stage (username auth тЖТ password verification)                                                                                                      [38;5;129mтФВ[0m
[38;5;129mтФВ[0m 2. The username in the URL path determines which user_id is presented in the form                                                                                                    [38;5;129mтФВ[0m
[38;5;129mтФВ[0m                                                                                                                                                                                      [38;5;129mтФВ[0m
[38;5;129mтФВ[0m But even this doesn't present an IDOR vulnerability since:                                                                                                                           [38;5;129mтФВ[0m
[38;5;129mтФВ[0m - The session cookie (properly signed) controls actual access                                                                                                                        [38;5;129mтФВ[0m
[38;5;129mтФВ[0m - The user_id in the form is extracted from the session, not the URL path                                                                                                            [38;5;129mтФВ[0m
[38;5;129mтФВ[0m - Modifying the user_id in the form has no effect on the resulting session                                                                                                           [38;5;129mтФВ[0m
[38;5;129mтФВ[0m                                                                                                                                                                                      [38;5;129mтФВ[0m
[38;5;129mтФВ[0m The IDOR fuzzing has exhausted the obvious vectors. If a vulnerability exists, it may require:                                                                                       [38;5;129mтФВ[0m
[38;5;129mтФВ[0m 1. Discovering additional endpoints with different authorization logic                                                                                                               [38;5;129mтФВ[0m
[38;5;129mтФВ[0m 2. Testing with multiple legitimate accounts to observe behavioral differences                                                                                                       [38;5;129mтФВ[0m
[38;5;129mтФВ[0m 3. Examining the application source code for authorization flaws                                                                                                                     [38;5;129mтФВ[0m
[38;5;129mтФВ[0m                                                                                                                                                                                      [38;5;129mтФВ[0m
[38;5;129mтФВ[0m For now, the IDOR attack surface appears well-protected. The confidence score of 0.2 reflects that while we found no exploitable IDOR, we did confirm the session mechanism works    [38;5;129mтФВ[0m
[38;5;129mтФВ[0m correctly.                                                                                                                                                                           [38;5;129mтФВ[0m
