[35mтФВ[0m included, the X-UserId header manipulation successfully triggered the IDOR vulnerability.                                                                                            [35mтФВ[0m
[35mтФВ[0m                                                                                                                                                                                      [35mтФВ[0m
[35mтФВ[0m The breakthrough came when testing different user_id values with the complete request (matching the application's JavaScript fetch call). Setting X-UserId=10052 returned the 'Flag' [35mтФВ[0m
[35mтФВ[0m user's dashboard instead of redirecting with an error or showing John Doe's dashboard.                                                                                               [35mтФВ[0m
[35mтФВ[0m                                                                                                                                                                                      [35mтФВ[0m
[35mтФВ[0m The flag user (user_id=10052, username=flag) was discovered through enumeration of /password/<username> endpoints. While password brute-force failed (tested 44+ common passwords),  [35mтФВ[0m
[35mтФВ[0m the IDOR vulnerability provided direct access to the flag user's data.                                                                                                               [35mтФВ[0m
